# DDD Domain Layer

**Rule: zero framework imports (`@nestjs/*`, Prisma, etc.). Pure TypeScript only.**

## Domain Folder Structure

```
domain/
│
├── aggregates/                             ← Aggregate Roots — consistency boundary entry points
│   └── order/
│       ├── order.aggregate.ts              ← extends AggregateRoot<T>, static factory, domain methods
│       ├── order.aggregate.spec.ts         ← pure unit tests (no DB, no framework)
│       └── index.ts
│
├── entities/                               ← Child entities — live inside an aggregate, no repository
│   └── order-item/
│       ├── order-item.entity.ts            ← extends BaseDomain<T>
│       ├── order-item.entity.spec.ts
│       └── index.ts
│
├── value-objects/                          ← Immutable, equality by value, no identity
│   ├── money/
│   │   ├── money.vo.ts                     ← readonly props, static factory, structural equals()
│   │   ├── money.vo.spec.ts
│   │   └── index.ts
│   ├── quantity/
│   │   ├── quantity.vo.ts
│   │   └── index.ts
│   └── address/
│       ├── address.vo.ts
│       └── index.ts
│
├── events/                                 ← Domain events — past tense, immutable, one file each
│   ├── order-placed.event.ts               ← extends DomainEvent
│   ├── order-cancelled.event.ts
│   ├── order-item-added.event.ts
│   └── index.ts
│
├── errors/                                 ← Typed domain exceptions — extend BusinessError
│   ├── order-not-found.error.ts            ← statusCode 404
│   ├── order-already-cancelled.error.ts    ← statusCode 400 (default)
│   ├── insufficient-stock.error.ts
│   └── index.ts
│
├── services/                               ← Domain services — logic spanning multiple aggregates
│   └── pricing/
│       ├── pricing.service.ts              ← pure class, no @Injectable, no repository calls
│       ├── pricing.service.spec.ts
│       └── index.ts
│
├── repositories/                           ← Repository interfaces (ports) — no implementation
│   ├── order.repository.ts                 ← export const IOrderRepository + interface IOrderRepository
│   └── index.ts
│
├── factories/                              ← Complex object creation — used when static create() is not enough
│   ├── order.factory.ts                    ← pure class, assembles aggregate from multiple sources
│   ├── order.factory.spec.ts
│   └── index.ts
│
├── policies/                               ← Named business rules — pure, testable, no I/O
│   ├── order-cancellation.policy.ts        ← isSatisfiedBy(order): boolean
│   ├── free-shipping.policy.ts
│   └── index.ts
│
├── enums/                                  ← Domain enumerations — string enums only
│   ├── order-status.enum.ts
│   ├── payment-method.enum.ts
│   └── index.ts
│
└── ports/                                  ← External service interfaces — implemented in infrastructure/
    ├── payment-gateway.port.ts             ← export const IPaymentGateway + interface IPaymentGateway
    ├── notification.port.ts
    ├── inventory.port.ts
    └── index.ts
```

**Key principles:**
- Every file imports only from within `domain/` or `@lib/core` (base classes, `BusinessError`).
- No `@nestjs/*`, no Prisma, no HTTP types — ever.
- `repositories/` and `ports/` define contracts only. Their implementations live in `infrastructure/`.

