## `aggregates/` — Aggregate Roots (`*.aggregate.ts`)

The only public entry point to a consistency boundary. Loaded and saved as one atomic unit by a repository. Emits domain events on every meaningful state transition.

**File layout:**
```
aggregates/
└── order/
    ├── order.aggregate.ts       ← the class
    ├── order.aggregate.spec.ts  ← pure unit tests (no DB, no framework)
    └── index.ts
```

**Rules:**
- Extends `AggregateRoot<T>` — always.
- All fields are ES private (`#`). Expose read-only values via getters only.
- Creation goes through a **static factory** (`static create(...)`) — never `new` from outside.
- Every mutating method: guard invariants → mutate field → `this.touch()` → `this.addDomainEvent(...)`.
- Throw a domain error from `domain/errors/` if an invariant is violated.

```ts
// ✅ GOOD
export class Order extends AggregateRoot<string> {
  #status: OrderStatus;
  #items: OrderItem[] = [];

  static create(data: { customerId: string }): Order {
    const order = new Order({ id: randomUUID(), status: OrderStatus.Pending, ...data });
    order.addDomainEvent(new OrderPlacedEvent(order));
    return order;
  }

  addItem(item: OrderItem): void {
    if (this.#status !== OrderStatus.Pending)
      throw new OrderAlreadyCancelledError(this.id);   // ← guard first
    this.#items.push(item);
    this.touch();
    this.addDomainEvent(new OrderItemAddedEvent(this));
  }

  cancel(): void {
    if (this.#status === OrderStatus.Cancelled)
      throw new OrderAlreadyCancelledError(this.id);
    this.#status = OrderStatus.Cancelled;
    this.touch();
    this.addDomainEvent(new OrderCancelledEvent(this));
  }

  get status() { return this.#status; }
  get items(): ReadonlyArray<OrderItem> { return this.#items; }
}

// ❌ BAD — public fields, public setter, no events, no invariant guard
export class Order {
  public status: OrderStatus;
  cancel() { this.status = OrderStatus.Cancelled; }
}
```

