## `entities/` — Child Entities (`*.entity.ts`)

Objects with identity that live **inside** an aggregate and are **never** loaded or saved independently.

**Rules:**
- Extends `BaseDomain<T>`.
- **No repository — ever.** Accessed only through the aggregate root.
- Never referenced from outside the aggregate boundary.

```ts
// ✅ Child entity — no repository, no domain events
export class OrderItem extends BaseDomain<string> {
  readonly #productId: string;
  #quantity: number;

  adjustQuantity(qty: number): void {
    if (qty <= 0) throw new InvalidQuantityError(qty);
    this.#quantity = qty;
    this.touch();
    // No event here — Order (the root) raises the event
  }

  get quantity() { return this.#quantity; }
}
```

