## `errors/` — Domain Errors (`*.error.ts`)

Typed exceptions that express **why a business rule was violated**.

**Rules:**
- One class per failure scenario, named after the violated rule.
- **Must extend `BusinessError`** from `@lib/core/exceptions/business-error`.
- Pass a human-readable `message` and a `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` `errorCode`.
- `statusCode` defaults to `400` — override only when semantically appropriate (e.g. `404`).
- Never throw raw `Error` or any NestJS `HttpException` from the domain layer.

```ts
// ✅ GOOD
import { BusinessError } from '@lib/core/exceptions/business-error';

export class OrderAlreadyCancelledError extends BusinessError {
  constructor(orderId: string) {
    super(`Order ${orderId} has already been cancelled.`, 'ORDER_ALREADY_CANCELLED');
  }
}

export class OrderNotFoundError extends BusinessError {
  constructor(orderId: string) {
    super(`Order ${orderId} not found.`, 'ORDER_NOT_FOUND', 404);
  }
}

// ❌ BAD — raw Error, no errorCode, not caught by GlobalExceptionFilter as a business error
export class OrderAlreadyCancelledError extends Error { ... }

// ❌ BAD — NestJS HttpException leaking into the domain layer
throw new BadRequestException('Order already cancelled');
```

