## `services/` — Domain Services

Logic that is domain logic but **does not naturally belong to a single aggregate** — e.g. calculations that span multiple roots or are shared across several commands.

**File layout:**
```
services/
└── pricing/
    ├── pricing.service.ts
    ├── pricing.service.spec.ts
    └── index.ts
```

**Rules:**
- No `@Injectable()`, no NestJS imports — pure TypeScript class.
- Does not call repositories — that is the application layer's job.
- If a method fits naturally on a single aggregate, put it there first.

```ts
// ✅ GOOD — pure domain service
export class PricingService {
  calculate(items: OrderItem[], discounts: Discount[]): Money {
    const subtotal = items.reduce(
      (sum, i) => sum.add(i.unitPrice.multiply(i.quantity)),
      Money.of(0, 'USD'),
    );
    return discounts.reduce((total, d) => d.apply(total), subtotal);
  }
}

// ❌ BAD — NestJS @Injectable() in the domain layer
@Injectable()
export class PricingService { ... }

// ❌ BAD — repository call inside a domain service
export class PricingService {
  constructor(private readonly productRepo: IProductRepository) {}
}
```

