## `policies/` — Domain Policies (`*.policy.ts`)

A single named business rule, encapsulated as a testable object.

**Rules:**
- No `@Injectable()` — pure domain class.
- Method name is a question: `isSatisfiedBy(entity)` or `canBeCancelled(order)`.
- Never perform I/O — evaluate only in-memory state.

```ts
// ✅ GOOD
export class OrderCancellationPolicy {
  isSatisfiedBy(order: Order): boolean {
    return order.status === OrderStatus.Pending
        && order.placedAt > subHours(new Date(), 24);
  }
}

// Usage:
if (!new OrderCancellationPolicy().isSatisfiedBy(order))
  throw new OrderCancellationNotAllowedError(order.id);
order.cancel();
```

