## `enums/` — Domain Enumerations (`*.enum.ts`)

**Rules:**
- **String enums only** — value is self-documenting in logs and DB columns.
- No business logic inside an enum — logic belongs in policies or aggregate methods.
- One enum per concept, one file per enum.

```ts
// ✅ GOOD
export enum OrderStatus {
  Pending   = 'PENDING',
  Confirmed = 'CONFIRMED',
  Cancelled = 'CANCELLED',
}

// ❌ BAD — numeric, opaque in logs and DB
export enum OrderStatus { Pending, Confirmed, Cancelled }
```

---

## `ports/` — External Service Ports (`*.port.ts`)

Interfaces for external services the domain needs (payment, notification, inventory). The domain defines the contract; infrastructure provides the implementation.

**Rules:**
- No `@Injectable()` — pure TypeScript interface.
- Define only what the domain needs — no infrastructure details (no Stripe types, no SDK imports).
- Same token naming rule as repositories: `Symbol` name = interface name.

```ts
// ✅ GOOD — no mention of Stripe, Twilio, etc.
export const IPaymentGateway = Symbol('IPaymentGateway');

export interface IPaymentGateway {
  charge(orderId: string, amount: Money): Promise<PaymentResult>;
  refund(paymentId: string): Promise<void>;
}

// Implemented in infrastructure/:
// @Injectable() export class StripePaymentGateway implements IPaymentGateway { ... }
```
